  ## Task 5.0: Core Daemon Orchestration — Summary
  
  ### Files created:
  1. **`src/colonyos/daemon.py`** — Core `Daemon` class with:
     - `start()` / `stop()` lifecycle with SIGINT/SIGTERM handling
     - `_slack_listener_thread()` — wraps existing Socket Mode
     - `_github_poller_thread()` — periodic issue polling with dedup
     - `_queue_executor_thread()` — priority-ordered queue drain (P0→P3, FIFO within tier, 24h starvation promotion)
     - `_scheduler_thread()` — CEO idle-fill (only when queue empty + cooldown elapsed) + cleanup scheduling
     - `_health_monitor_thread()` — heartbeat + budget threshold alerts
     - Budget enforcement: daily cap check before each run, auto-pause on exhaustion, midnight UTC reset
     - Circuit breaker: consecutive failure tracking, auto-cooldown
     - Startup crash recovery: orphaned RUNNING items → FAILED, git state validation
     - PID lock file to prevent duplicate instances
     - `get_health_status()` for `/healthz` endpoint integration
  
